de.wwu.muggl.ui.gui.support
Class StaticGuiSupport

java.lang.Object
  de.wwu.muggl.ui.gui.support.StaticGuiSupport

public final class StaticGuiSupport
extends java.lang.Object

This class offers a couple of often needed methods and constants for the GUI, especially to show message boxes and to calculate the needed size and position of windows. It cannot be instantiated.

Version:
1.0.0, 2010-03-18
Author:
Tim Majchrzak

Method Detail

showMessageBox

public static int showMessageBox(org.eclipse.swt.widgets.Shell shell,
                                 java.lang.String message)
Show a message box in the Shell shell with the supplied Message. The window title will be "Information", it will provide an "OK"-Button and have an Information-Icon. This Method is overloaded and offers two more customizable alternatives.

Parameters:
shell - The Shell to display the message box in.
message - The message that box is to be filled with.
Returns:
The response from the message box as an int.

showMessageBox

public static int showMessageBox(org.eclipse.swt.widgets.Shell shell,
                                 java.lang.String message,
                                 int type)
Show a message box in the Shell shell with the supplied Message. The window title will be "Information", while its' style is determind by the supplied parameter type. This Method is overloaded and offers one more simply and one more customizable alternatives.

Parameters:
shell - The Shell to display the message box in.
message - The message that box is to be filled with.
type - The type of the message box.
Returns:
The response from the message box as an int.

processGuiError

public static void processGuiError(java.lang.Throwable t,
                                   java.lang.String windowName,
                                   org.eclipse.swt.widgets.Shell shell)
Process an error that requires a window of the gui to be closed. The Throwable is processed, the logging is differentiated between Exceptions and Errors. Also a message box is generated, informing the user what has happened.

Parameters:
t - The Throwable to process.
windowName - The windows' name that is to be inserted into the message.
shell - The Shell to display the message box in. Should be the Shell of the parent window of the "crashing" one.

public static java.lang.String formatNumericValue(java.lang.String numericValue,

Format a numeric value. Numeric values must be the String representations of double, float, int or long values. Other, especially pre-formated input values will lead to unexpected results.

maxDecimalPlaces - The maximum decimal places. Rounding will be used.
Returns:
The formated value.

computeRunningTime

public static java.lang.String computeRunningTime(long timeRun,
                                                  boolean accuracyWarning)
Return a String representation of the current running time. It will contain detailed time information in the form days, hours, minutes, seconds, miliseconds. Values that are zero wil not be shown.

Parameters:
timeRun - The running time to compute.
accuracyWarning - If set to true, a warning regarding the accuracy will be appended if the time is below one second.
Returns:
A String representation of the current running time, or "infinite", if the time value is -1.

getFormatedIndexNumber

public static java.lang.String getFormatedIndexNumber(int lineNumber,
                                                      int lineNumberLength,
                                                      boolean addColon)
Get the formated String for a line number for a set line number length.

Parameters:
lineNumber - The line number to format.
lineNumberLength - The desired length (without ": ").
addColon - Toggles whether a colon and a space is inserted to finish the line.
Returns:
The formated line number.

getFormatedIndexNumberByMaximumNumber

public static java.lang.String getFormatedIndexNumberByMaximumNumber(int lineNumber,
                                                                     int maximumNumber,
                                                                     boolean addColon)
Call getFormatedIndexNumber(lineNumber, lineNumberLength, addColon) with a lineNumberLength calculated from the maximum number that will be encountered. For this, simply the length of the String representation of the number is taken.

Parameters:
lineNumber - The line number to format.
maximumNumber - The maximum number that the line number is generated in relation to.
addColon - Toggles wheteher a colon and a space is inserted to finish the line.
Returns:
The formated line number.
